intro: Phryganocydia corymbosa, commonly known as the clustered erinaceus, is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae. It is characterized by its compact growth habit and small, clustered inflorescences. The plant produces white to pale yellow flowers that bloom in late summer. It is native to parts of Europe and is often found in grassy habitats. The foliage is aromatic, with a distinct scent that is characteristic of the Apiaceae family.
